14 WHEREAS, the internationally recognized housing program Habitat for Humanity
15 International was founded and still maintains its headquarters in the City of Americus; and
16 WHEREAS, Americus-Sumter County is home to South Georgia Technical College and
17 Georgia Southwestern State University, both of which contribute to Georgia's workforce in
18 significant ways; and
19 WHEREAS, Americus-Sumter County is a leading producer of Georgia's cotton, peanuts,
20 and vegetables as well as a significant producer of livestock; and
21 WHEREAS, the Sumter County City of Plains is home to the 39th President of the United
22 States, the late Jimmy Carter, and to the late First Lady Rosalynn Carter, who together
23 brought international attention to Sumter County, Georgia.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
25 commend Americus-Sumter County for its many contributions to the State of Georgia and
26 recognize February 19, 2025, as Americus-Sumter County Day at the state capitol.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
28 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
29 press.
